  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Student cognitive modeling has a series of downstream applications, among which the two most representative types are educational recommendation systems and Computerized Adaptive Testing (CAT).",
    "Educational recommendation systems aim to recommend relevant learning resources for students, such as learning path recommendation [8][9][10]109], course recommendation [110,111], and exercise recommendation [11,112,113].",
    "CAT aims to provide tests that adapt dynamically to each student by tailoring test exercises based on the student's performance [114].The CD model is an essential component of CAT, as CAT requires CD to continuously assess students' cognitive states [115,116].",
    "In the future, we may consider integrating models of downstream applications based on student cognitive modeling.",
    "• Refine and update the eco-services promptly."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
